	Expert: Expert Mode
	Master: Master Mode
	Legendary: Legendary Mode
	Revengence: Revengence Mode
	Death: Death Mode
	LDeath: Malice Mode
	Infernum: Infernum Mode
	MInfernum: Ragnarok Mode
	WarningSouls:
		'''
		WARNING: Fargo's Souls Mod is NOT compatible with Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!
		Enabling Infernum Mode or Ragnarok mode will disable Eternity mode as they are incompatible!
		Please do not report any balance issues or bugs while playing with Fargo's Souls.
		'''
	WarningForTheWorthyON:
		'''
		WARNING: The For the Worthy seed is NOT compatible with Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!
		Both the Infernum and Ragnarok difficulties will be disabled in this seed!
		Please do not report any balance issues or bugs while playing in the For The Worthy seed.
		'''
	WarningForTheWorthyOFF:
		'''
		WARNING: The For the Worthy seed is NOT compatible with Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!
		Please do not report any balance issues or bugs while playing in the For The Worthy seed.
		'''
	NoticeHomewardRagnarok:
		'''
		Thanks for playing Homeward Ragnarok, an official DLC mod to Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!
		Please report and issues relating to Homeward Journey in the Homeward Ragnarok discord.
		The main team does not directly work on this mod and can not provide help in the main discord.
		You can turn off this popup in the Homeward Config in the Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok config.
		'''
	NoticeHomewardJourney:
		'''
		NOTICE: It is detected that you have Homeward Journey enabled!
		We highly recommend you to install the "Homeward Ragnarok" mod for compatibility between these mods before proceeding!
		Homeward Ragnarok also adds new content and other optional reworks for Homeward Journey content!
		You can turn off this popup in the Homeward Config in the Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok config.
		'''
	DevNoticeCampsiteFix: Flag pole crash fix applied
}

DifficultyUI: {
	Name: Ragnarok
	ShortDescription:
		'''
		[c/B32E81:An extreme version of Infernum and the intended difficulty of Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok.]
		[c/B32E81:This mode does not work with the For the Worthy seed.]
		'''
	ExpandedDescription:
		'''
		[c/B32E81:Seemlessly merges both Death and Infernum mode, combining many of their changes.]
		[c/B32E81:Many major foes will have unique behavior patterns on top of their Infernum AI.]
		[c/B32E81:Foes will have very high base stats and scale more agressively in multiplayer.]
		[c/FF0055:Can you master the Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok?]
		'''
	Activation: The Infernal Eclipse has risen...
	Deactivation: Another unworthy challenger has walked away.
	MasterToggle: Master mode is now enabled!
}

WelcomeMessage: {
	Welcome: Welcome to the Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok Mod Pack!
	TBRNotice: NOTICE: It is detected that you have Thorium Helheim enabled! Make sure the Health, Damage, & Speed multipliers are set to 1 in the compatibility config (unless you want a harder experience) as this mod automatically adjusts the Thorium bosses depending on the current difficulty.
	TBRWarning: WARNING: It is detected that you do not have Thorium Helheim enabled! This mod is heavily recommended as it rebalances Thorium Bosses to have mechanics more in-line with Infernum mode and Calamity in general.
	RagWarning: WARNING: It is detected that you do not have Ragnarok enabled! Without this mod, Thorium & Calamity may not work well together. It is heavily recommended you enable this mod for a more complete & balanced experience
	EventTrophyNotice: NOTICE: It is detected that you do not have More Trophies and Relics enabled! Without this mod, any bosses that aren't from Vanilla, Calamity, or Infernum may not have Calamity lore or Infernum intros. It is heavily recommended you enable this mod for a more complete & balanced experience.
	SoulsWarning:
		'''
		WARNING: Fargo's Souls Mod is NOT compatible with Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok! 
		Please note that Infernum Mode is not compatiable with Eternity Mode and you may expirence major bugs if you have both enabled.
		'''
	OverhaulWarning: WARNING: It is detected that you have the Calamity Overhaul enabled! This mod is very buggy and will cause a lot of issues. We heavily recommend you disable this mod.
	RemnantsWarning: WARNING: It is detected that you have the Remnants mod enabled! This mod is NOT compatible with Infernum If this world was generated with the mod, please regenerate it with this mod off, or otherwise do not report bugs about world generation.
	MasterPatchNotice: NOTICE: It is detected that you have the Infernum Master Patch mod enabled. This mod is redunant with this mod and can be disabled.
	CalMinusNotice: NOTICE: It is detected that you have the Calamity Minus Mod enabled! This mod already includes all of the mods features while you have Calamaity Balance Changes on in the Infernal Eclipse of Raganrok config.
	CalBalNotice: NOTICE: It is detected that you have the Calamity Balance Changes Mod enabled! This mod already includes most of the mods features that are listed on their Steam Workshop page, while you have Calamaity Balance Changes on in the Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok config. Calamity Balance Changes also adds a bunch of unlisted changes which might make your playthough worse than intended.
	InfernumActive: The prodigy has returned to face the Infernal Eclipse...
	MPConnect: A prodigy has returned to help face the Infernal Eclipse...
	InfernumForced: Infernal energy has been infused into this world...
	RagnarokBalance: NOTICE: For the Balancing of weapons to be as intended, set the Ragnarok mod config of 'Generic Weapon Tweaks' to OFF, as otherwise the changes will stack and weapons will be far stronger than intended.
	RagnarokRework: NOTICE: It is detected that you have both the Ragnarok mod and Thorium Bosses Reworked enabled. For the intended experience, turn all the boss toggles in the Ragnarok Boss Config to Thorium Bosses Reworked.
	GulaVaultMessage: The vault refuses to open. A stronger evil must be defeated first...
	LichMessage: The objects magic still seems to be frozen inside. Maybe the structure in the snow biome will help uncover why?
}

