			'''
		Lore: After Erelian had obtained the Exo Prism from Draedon, he finnaly had everything to perfect his suit's spirit AI - and now the tyrant was finnally in his sights.
	}

	Lore: {
		MysteriousDiary.DisplayName: Mysterious Diary

		LorePolaris: {
			DisplayName: Polaris
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Every time Draedon invented a new technology, he would apply it to his passion: making deadly machines of war.
				This was one of his first creations after arriving on this planet and my service, having just created stable levitation to imbue his machines.
				While a novelty at the time, it soon revealed itself to be impractical for any real use on a battlefield.
				As such, I ordered Permafrost to get rid of it. It would seem instead of destroying it, he sealed it away in a prison of ice, locked away for eternity.
				Ironic, isn’t it? The fate that we push unto others often becomes our own.
				'''
		}

		LoreAdvisor: {
			DisplayName: The Advisor
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				During his early experiments attempting to interact with, contain, and exploit the natural spirits that inhabit these lands, 
				Draedon found early success with the spirits that lingered in the upper atmosphere of our planet.
				Naming them ‘Otherworldly’ spirits as a homage to his origins, he aimed higher, making a more powerful body for the spirit to inhabit, 
				but the experiment backfired, and left with no choice, he had several other constructs keep it in place and constantly drain it of it’s power. 
				'''
		}

		LoreGlowmoth: {
			DisplayName: Glowmoth
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				It’s no surprise that you would find one of these creatures here.
				The mushrooms provide energy for the moth, and the moth helps to spread the mushrooms; in balance, as nature should be...
				Although, there does seem to be some latent void energy surrounding the creature.
				How... peculiar.
				'''
		}

		LoreLux: {
			DisplayName: Lux
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				While the Hallow has many that protect it, chaos spirits have no equal.
				None of them had ever been sufficiently weakened for intelligent use,
				and Draedon ended up shoving them into constructs for the sole purpose of containment.
				With this in mind, it is odd that collector once again came to absorb what was left of its energy after its defeat.
				How quaint.
				'''
		}

		LorePharaoh: {
			DisplayName: Pharaoh's Curse
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Upon their older sister - Otonilou, the Goddess of Electricity — meeting her end at the hands of Calamitas, 
				her younger brother was left to lead Ilmeris on his own.
				Unlike his sister, who slayed a dragon for her power, his heart was pure, yet still shares a saddening fate.
				His people surrounded on all sides by kingdoms lead by dragon slayers with stolen power, in desperation he instead turned to that 'void' magic.
				The meddling of his void haunts him even after death; him and his people bound to his tomb.
				This marks the beginning of the true downfall of Ilmeris, of which I played a large role in.
				'''
		}

		LorePutrid: {
			DisplayName: Putrid Pinky
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				One of Draedon's experiments. 
				This creature is one of his attempts to understand the inherent divinity that is present is all slimes, 
				no matter how minuscule it might be.
				He did manage to successfully draw out the latent energy, but somehow in the process, 
				gave the creature an endless hunger for peanuts of all things, and it provoked rapid and uncontrollable growth.
				It quickly escaped containment, and then you know the rest.
				'''
		}

		LoreSerpent: {
			DisplayName: Subspace Serpent
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				There lies tales of mysterious serpent‑like beings that roam the manifold between dimensions.
				Many say that they are too dangerous to face alone,
				and that they could kill anyone within an instant with the void energy they possess.
				This one, however... is clearly juvenile.
				'''
		}

		LoreProvi: {
			DisplayName: The Radiant One
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				I dreamt of peace once. I don't know why I did.
				Ever since I received word that there was something beyond this world,
				I've have felt that womans presence in our world every now and again.
				Now what Thorne wanted from her? Who knows.
				But all the power is in your hands now, Terrarian.
				'''
		}

		LoreMirror: {
			DisplayName: The Mirror
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				I stared into it for a long while, but like any other mirror, I only saw myself.
				But even then, something felt... different. It felt wrong, almost... twisted.
				I disregarded it. But even now, I can feel the piercing gaze my reflection had... shooting directly through my skull.
				Once you come so far, the hardest part of your journey is facing yourself.
				'''
		}

		LoreDylan: {
			DisplayName: Dylan
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Hmm ... I'm surprised that you even know of that person.
				The first time we found him we thought he was a god ... however, ends up he didn't actually have a auric soul.
				We took him in and he showed us how to make powerful elemental imbued gear and bombs that wasn't just steel.
				His ideas had helped increase my army's power by a lot, but he never fought himself.

				One day when I went to his room, but nothing was there expect from a note.
				We couldn't translate his writing but from the pictures it was some sort of ring,
				with one of the key ingredients appering to be a "Dark Sun Ring."
				Perhaps that "Guide" could help you further decipher this note.
				Regardless, I'm sure you'll figure out how to make it.

				–Stay tuned for the future of Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!–
				'''
		}

		LoreMjolnir: {
			DisplayName: Mjolnir
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Thor, one of the many gods that had managed to evade my crusade,
				yet he will never forget what I had done to him and family.
				Asgard was merely a land of sinners, so I merely did what they had done to so many others.
				Thor had escaped me and I belived he still ruled over Asgard to this day,
				but with his hammer in your hands, perhaps it is no more.
				'''
		}

		LorePrimordials: {
			DisplayName: The Primordials
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Before the world was formed, there were only the Primordials.
				Each of them represents an aspect of this world, and protect the world from Ragnarok.
				During my war, I had wanted to slay them thinking they were merely sinners like the other gods,
				however no matter what I did I could not get there attention.
				Was I not worthy of their attention despite all I had done to the world?
				Don't tell me they think I'm a spec in this worlds history compared to you...
				'''
		}

		LoreThunderBird: {
			DisplayName: The Grand Thunder Bird
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				First spotted near the conclusion of the draconic era, it was assumed that these birds,
				like many other creatures being discovered at the time, had draconic blood in them;
				a fact that was hard to disprove given the way they absorbed the pure light from Zeratros’ sun, 
				and converted the energy into lightning.
				At the time, they were likely the strongest non-divine creatures on the planet.
				Alas… a combination of a lack of predators and the Traitor Almighty taking control over the sun 
				has left this once magnificent species a husk of their former selves.
				'''
		}

		LoreRagnarok: {
			DisplayName: Ragnarok
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				How curious.
				Ragnarok, the fabled end of days, was a being rather than an event.
				I had searched the world for how to start it, so I could destroy Asgard,
				but in the end, I had found nothing.
				The tales of serpents and fire were far from the truth,
				but now Ragnarok lies in ruin just like Asgard itself.

				You are now seen as the hero for this land, 
				and may you find peace in the new age you have created.
				However, beware, for with every end comes a new beginning...
				[c/7C0A02:Do not push your luck further, Terrarian.]
				'''
		}

		LoreMegalomaniac: {
			DisplayName: The Megalomaniac
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				The Devourer, the Dragon, and the Witch. All fell to your ambition. Your motive. Your drive.
				I had an ambition similar. But never was I deemed hero.
				I freed this world of tyranny, and yet I stand known as a tyrant.
				Now one with a determination like mine arrives hell-bent on my destruction.
				I will meet the same fate the oppressor I felled had.
				Destined to be dispatched of by one with similar aspirations as themself.
				I should have known, realized it sooner. It was always meant to be this way.
				'''
		}

		LoreAnniversaryOne: {
			DisplayName: Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok
			Tooltip: Greatly boosts passive luck while in your inventory
			Lore:
				'''
				What started as a small project I put together just for myself and a few friends has slowly grown into something much bigger than I ever expected. 
				Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok began as a way to make a chaotic mix of mods actually feel playable together by
				just tweaking things here and there so my playthrough at the time would fell smoother and more fun. 
				But over time, those small fixes turned into full systems, then into reworks, and eventually into an entire framework for how the game should feel. 
				I found myself not just patching things, but designing—rethinking progression, balancing classes across multiple mods, 
				and building something that felt cohesive instead of stitched together. 
				It's been a long process of trial, frustration, and iteration, especially learning how to make everything work in multiplayer 
				and across so many different mods, but it's also been incredibly rewarding. 
				What was once just a personal project has become a full-scale development effort with its own identity, and honestly, 
				seeing it grow into something others can enjoy has been one of the most fulfilling parts of the journey.

				Thank you to everyone who has supported the mod, given feedback, and been part of this community.
				Here's to many more updates, features, and chaotic times in the world of Infernal Eclipse of Ragnarok!
				'''
		}

		LoreAbominationn: {
			DisplayName: Abominationn
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				The middle child of the eternal siblings, and one of the laziest beings I've ever seen.
				While the Abominationn has the ability to fully control the weather and fully turn away invaders, 
				he truly is super lazy, going to the point of even fusing his weapons to his hands.
				He weilds a weapon that has the ability to divide the soul itself, on top of being able to use all supernatural phenomena. 
				Good thing for you he choose not to use any celestial attacks out of respect of the Mutant, or else your victory might have not been possible.
				'''
		}

		LoreDeviantt: {
			DisplayName: Deviantt
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				The youngest of the eternal siblings, and also the weakest.
				She has collected a bunch of rare monster items throughout her journey and when in a helping mood, she will sell them to others.
				However, when she isn't in a helping mood, she fully expresses her lovestruck sadism.
				The Deviantt has the ability to cast spells using the both the primordial light and pure love, all while weilding a living axe made of evil.
				Even though you bested her in combat, she seems to not fear death, and this is the first time I have ever seen her go all out in a fight.
				'''
		}

		LoreMutant: {
			DisplayName: Mutant
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				The oldest and strongest of the eternal siblings.
				While the other siblings calls the Mutant their brother, he personally refuses to confirm his gender.
				He is the keeper of eternity, with ultimate power incarnate, and is believed to have come from another world beyond that dimensional rift.
				Other than you, he is the strongest being to ever grace the land of Terraria, with master of dominion over every aspect to combat.
				Even though he had all this power, he always was more interested in watching other battles in the world than partake in any himself. 
				He always told people that he was looking for someone strong and it looks like he found the person he was looking for.
				'''
		}

		LoreLepus: {
			DisplayName: Lepus
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				The bunnies of this world are strangely adaptable. They can take on many forms, and absorb all sorts of energy.
				This one in particular seems to have been a pet of a minor god of revelry and celebration before he was slain by my army’s hand.
				'''
		}

		LoreTurkor: {
			DisplayName: Turkor The Ungrateful
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Vengeful souls are curious beings.
				For a soul to remain in this life after death without external magic requires either an extraordinary strong will, or a burning rage within.
				I know not whom this was in life, nor how they perished.
				While spirits can exert force on their own, it is only when they take a vessel that they gain true power.
				This soul is no different, their power amplified by the unjust killing of this turkey; that was once destined for a royal feast, 
				with food that most commoners would never have the chance to try.
				Be wary of wrathful souls, for when you are the target of their rage, their power can rival or even surpass gods.
				'''
		}

		LoreOcram: {
			DisplayName: Ocram
			Tooltip: ""
			Lore:
				'''
				Before the Gods had a firm grasp of the Underworld and Azafure was fully established,
				there was a time where many parties vied for control over that fabled magma crevice.
				The most notable being a powerful archdemon who commanded the demons into a clan of civilization-stomping ravagers.
				When the Gods finally set their sights on the Underworld, his band was quashed, slaughtered one by one.
				However, the archdemon survived no matter the Gods' attacks, much to their chagrin,
				so they settled for torturously mutilating him in a way that drove him to insanity, and then he was discarded.
				His name was long forgotten, to the point where I had never heard it spoken in my lifetime.
				Yet, upon seeing that fiend, I am certain Ocram was that fallen archdemon from an age beyond my own.
				If I had known of its continued existence during my glory days, I would have attempted to do what the Gods could not - or would not.
				'''
		}
	}

